[
    {
        "content": "<p>I tried to implement <code>seek()</code> for <code>FileOperation</code>. After I return new value of the offset, I find that the file offset won't change, which is the same as C version of FileOperation. But this time in Rust, I can't find a appropriate to change the <code>offset</code> of <code>file</code> to make <code>seek()</code> really work. Any ways? Or it is under construction? <span aria-label=\"blush\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f60a\" role=\"img\" title=\"blush\">:blush:</span></p>",
        "id": 276444202,
        "sender_full_name": "SocialistDalao",
        "timestamp": 1648110712
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Can you show your code?</p>",
        "id": 276462655,
        "sender_full_name": "Wei Liu",
        "timestamp": 1648121905
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm reading the source code now. I think that it may be the problem from my implementation. I'll check it first. <span aria-label=\"sob\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f62d\" role=\"img\" title=\"sob\">:sob:</span></p>",
        "id": 276467256,
        "sender_full_name": "SocialistDalao",
        "timestamp": 1648124672
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In <code>FileOperationsVtable::llseek_callback()</code>, it doesn't change the file offset like <code>write_callback()</code> and <code>read_callback()</code> does. The source codes are as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">extern</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"C\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">llseek_callback</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">file</span>: <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">offset</span>: <span class=\"nc\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">loff_t</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">whence</span>: <span class=\"nc\">c_types</span>::<span class=\"n\">c_int</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">loff_t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">from_kernel_result</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">off</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">whence</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.};</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span>::<span class=\"n\">Wrapper</span>::<span class=\"n\">borrow</span><span class=\"p\">((</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">private_data</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">off</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span>::<span class=\"n\">seek</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">FileRef</span>::<span class=\"n\">from_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">},</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">off</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"c1\">// NO change of offset here</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">off</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">loff_t</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 276470352,
        "sender_full_name": "SocialistDalao",
        "timestamp": 1648126285
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Why do you need offset to be modified? I think the rust code is just trying to follow the callback definitions in Linux here.</p>",
        "id": 276471400,
        "sender_full_name": "Wei Liu",
        "timestamp": 1648126756
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In device drivers by C, after we handle the <code>read()</code> or <code>write()</code>, we will modify the file offset from given <code>loff_t *f_pos</code>. In Rust version now, the interface only provides immutable reference <code>&amp;File</code>, and the abstraction behind will modify the <code>offset</code> for us. But in <code>seek</code>, the abstraction doesn't perform like that. This is what makes me feel confused.</p>\n<p>write_callback() and read_callback() source codes:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">extern</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"C\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">write_callback</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">file</span>: <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">buf</span>: <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c_types</span>::<span class=\"n\">c_char</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">len</span>: <span class=\"nc\">c_types</span>::<span class=\"n\">c_size_t</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">offset</span>: <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">loff_t</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">c_types</span>::<span class=\"n\">c_ssize_t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">from_kernel_result</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">UserSlicePtr</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">buf</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c_types</span>::<span class=\"n\">c_void</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">reader</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span>::<span class=\"n\">Wrapper</span>::<span class=\"n\">borrow</span><span class=\"p\">((</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">private_data</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">written</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span>::<span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">FileRef</span>::<span class=\"n\">from_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">},</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}.</span><span class=\"n\">try_into</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"c1\">// Modify offset here</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">loff_t</span>::<span class=\"n\">try_from</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">written</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">written</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">extern</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"C\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">read_callback</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">file</span>: <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">buf</span>: <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c_types</span>::<span class=\"n\">c_char</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">len</span>: <span class=\"nc\">c_types</span>::<span class=\"n\">c_size_t</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">offset</span>: <span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">loff_t</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">c_types</span>::<span class=\"n\">c_ssize_t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">from_kernel_result</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">UserSlicePtr</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">buf</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c_types</span>::<span class=\"n\">c_void</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">writer</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span>::<span class=\"n\">Wrapper</span>::<span class=\"n\">borrow</span><span class=\"p\">((</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">private_data</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">read</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span>::<span class=\"n\">read</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">FileRef</span>::<span class=\"n\">from_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">file</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">},</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}.</span><span class=\"n\">try_into</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"c1\">// Modify offset here</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">offset</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">loff_t</span>::<span class=\"n\">try_from</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">read</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">read</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 276472519,
        "sender_full_name": "SocialistDalao",
        "timestamp": 1648127233
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The same goes for C implementation of <code>seek</code>. It does not modify offset.</p>",
        "id": 276473214,
        "sender_full_name": "Wei Liu",
        "timestamp": 1648127543
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is how <code>llseek</code> is defined in <code>fs.h</code> -- <code>loff_t (*llseek) (struct file *, loff_t, int);</code></p>",
        "id": 276473270,
        "sender_full_name": "Wei Liu",
        "timestamp": 1648127584
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Notice the second argument is of type <code>loff_t</code>, not <code>loff_t *</code>.</p>",
        "id": 276473326,
        "sender_full_name": "Wei Liu",
        "timestamp": 1648127620
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But <code>read</code> and <code>write</code> do take <code>loff_t *</code>. That's why I said the rust code is just following the C code.</p>",
        "id": 276473419,
        "sender_full_name": "Wei Liu",
        "timestamp": 1648127648
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think my rust knowledge is a bit rusty (pun intended). It is interesting that <code>read</code> and <code>write</code> do <code>unsafe { *offset }.try_into()?</code> for the pointer.</p>",
        "id": 276473836,
        "sender_full_name": "Wei Liu",
        "timestamp": 1648127837
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It seems that I've got it wrong! Thank you very much. <span aria-label=\"+1\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"+1\">:+1:</span></p>",
        "id": 276474009,
        "sender_full_name": "SocialistDalao",
        "timestamp": 1648127924
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well... I don't know why this is the case. It's the source code from Rust for Linux, not mine. I'm a newborn baby here to learn something interesting.</p>",
        "id": 276474259,
        "sender_full_name": "SocialistDalao",
        "timestamp": 1648128047
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But... I want to modify the <code>file-&gt;f_pos</code> because I need to change the file offset to let <code>lseek()</code> work. If not, the file won't change after user programs invoke <code>lseek()</code>. But interface in Rust only provides immutable reference, there is no way to achieve that.</p>",
        "id": 276475417,
        "sender_full_name": "SocialistDalao",
        "timestamp": 1648128662
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I took a look at <code>fs/read_write.c loff_t default_llseek(struct file *file, loff_t offset, int whence)</code> just now. It modifies the <code>file-&gt;f_pos</code> at last, which means there is need to modify the offset. Hope I get everything clear and right. <span aria-label=\"persevere\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f623\" role=\"img\" title=\"persevere\">:persevere:</span></p>",
        "id": 276475899,
        "sender_full_name": "SocialistDalao",
        "timestamp": 1648128927
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think you will need to put the code that changes <code>f_pos</code> into your <code>impl file::Operations for YOUR_TYPE</code></p>",
        "id": 276480845,
        "sender_full_name": "Wei Liu",
        "timestamp": 1648131188
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But I think you know that already. Your issue is with the immutable reference.</p>",
        "id": 276480932,
        "sender_full_name": "Wei Liu",
        "timestamp": 1648131235
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Exactly. I don't want to change the interface provided by the Rust for Linux. And I want to mention that no examples implement <code>seek()</code> in Rust for Linux now, as I discovered.</p>",
        "id": 276571954,
        "sender_full_name": "SocialistDalao",
        "timestamp": 1648178280
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This means, the <code>seek()</code> only returns error to tell the caller that it doesn't support this feature.</p>",
        "id": 276572037,
        "sender_full_name": "SocialistDalao",
        "timestamp": 1648178356
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can open an issue on Github. If you're the first user using <code>seek</code>, it would be surprised you manage to find deficiencies.</p>",
        "id": 276603341,
        "sender_full_name": "Wei Liu",
        "timestamp": 1648206403
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I had noticed this issue with <code>seek</code> and discussed it with <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411477\">@Miguel Ojeda</span> a couple of weeks ago. We decided then to look into allowing one of the several implementations from read_write.c plus a customised one.</p>\n<p>Before we get to this, I think what we can do is add a <code>set_pos()</code> method to <code>File</code>, this would allow us to implement <code>seek</code> as it is now</p>",
        "id": 276611675,
        "sender_full_name": "Wedson Almeida Filho (Old Google account)",
        "timestamp": 1648211606
